{
  "title": "HTML <option> Tag",
  "content": [
    {
      "heading": "<option> Tag",
      "paragraphs": [
        "The <option> tag defines an option in a select list.",
        "Example: <select id=\"cars\">\n  <option value=\"volvo\">Volvo</option>\n  <option value=\"saab\">Saab</option>\n</select>"
      ]
    },
    {
      "heading": "Definition and Usage",
      "paragraphs": [
        "Used inside <select>, <optgroup>, or <datalist>.",
        "The value attribute specifies data sent on form submission.",
        "Group options with <optgroup> for long lists."
      ]
    },
    {
      "heading": "Browser Support",
      "paragraphs": [
        "Supported by all major browsers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "heading": "Attributes",
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "table": {
            "headers": ["Attribute", "Value", "Description"],
            "rows": [
              ["value", "text", "Data sent to server"],
              ["selected", "selected", "Pre-selects option"],
              ["disabled", "disabled", "Disables option"]
            ]
          }
        },
        "Supports global and event attributes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "heading": "Examples",
      "paragraphs": [
        "In datalist: <input list=\"browsers\">\n<datalist id=\"browsers\">\n  <option value=\"Chrome\">\n  <option value=\"Firefox\">\n</datalist>",
        "With optgroup: <select>\n  <optgroup label=\"Swedish Cars\">\n    <option value=\"volvo\">Volvo</option>\n  </optgroup>\n</select>"
      ]
    },
    {
      "heading": "Default CSS",
      "paragraphs": [
        "None"
      ]
    }
  ]
}